This on the best little street in brentwood, it has a number of great little spots, like the yogurt shoppe, an italian bistro/cafe, a pizza spot, a bakery, a few necessity spots (cobbler, dry-cleaned), and of course the Starbucks on the corner. < review>
If I could give this location zero stars I would. I don’t know if I just happen to be getting the worse service over and over again by chance but I’ve lived  right next door to this one for 3 years and I literally drive out of my way to avoid going to it. Today was a perfect example, I was rushing so I stopped in, ordered a cold brew and sausage egg and cheese, waited ten minutes for them to tell me they don’t have any more breakfast sandwiches (going off the time stamp on the cup) now I’m late. If stuff like this didn’t happen to me every 4/5 times over three years (mainly either forgetting or not knowing they’re out of something) I wouldn’t feel so compelled to write a bad review right now.< /review>

<review>We had a day trip from SF to Napa valley on the 8 pax limo provided by this company. Overall we loved their services.

The staff:
The office staff were always very responsive to our phone call, and always called us back shortly when if he was not able to take the call. He patiently describes the details and answered all the questions I have respectfully, which I was very happy about and felt very reliable.

The driver:
The driver was very kind and responsive, too. He drove very safely but on time. After we finish visiting certain place, all we have to do is call him and he'll take the call in 3 seconds, and will come to pick us up in a few minutes. For whatever sudden request such as asking to go to bathroom when we're on the highway, he drove to the closest gas station without making too much workaround, which saved our time a lot.

Note: Make sure you pay the gratuity *directly* to the driver, to avoid extra processing cost later on. The staff will make it very clear when you book, and this is also clearly written on the contract.<//review>< Pictures>

<time>1468461329914<//time><rate>5</rate><review>John, the owner of Anthem, is a really nice man!  His services were excellent. Picked us (a party of 8) up in Vallejo on time to go to the Napa wineries!  He even helped us calculate an appropriate departure time, and we successfully relied on him to remind us on when leave for the next winery--which I liked because we could just focus on having a great time. <text>John is awesome!  I was tempted to go with some of the larger limo companies that frequently tour the Napa region, but I am so glad I stuck with John.  He emailed me several times prior to us arriving in Vallejo, was early to pick us up, and he was extremely personable throughout the trip.

We ended up at the Napa/Sonoma border at Pride Mountain which was breathtaking.  However, traffic was majorly backed up on all roads back to Vallejo which caused us to miss our ferry back to San Francisco.  John drove us to the ferry to try to see if we could still make it, then when we realized we were too late, John changed his plans and drove us another 2 hours back to San Francisco (heavy traffic all the way).

He stayed positive throughout (which was helpful because I was mad at myself for missing the last ferry), and he drove us all the way back to our hotel in downtown San Francisco, which meant he also had to drive all the way back to Napa to get back home.

He was very affordable (more competitive than almost all other limo companies), and he recently purchased a black limo that handled the steep trek to Pride Mountain with ease.  Thank you so much John for making our day so enjoyable! <Review>WOW! THEY ARE SO GOOD! HIGHLY RECOMMEND!
My wife and I were driving our Pleasureway from Astoria, Oregon to San Juan Capistrano, CA., making a short stop in Santa Barbara for a quick visit with family, when the engine died. I had it towed to Kennedy's after doing a brief search on my phone for area mechanics. If you have ever been in a similar situation you know how completely daunting (and scary) that can be. There was something about talking with Angela on the phone that made it feel right to have it towed to this shop. Once there, talking to Fidel convinced me it was a good decision. That was just the beginning! They got the van late in the afternoon and I was really concerned because losing a day or more travel time was going to be a problem for our schedule. Fidel told me that if it was something that could be done in just a few hours, and if parts were available, that he would stay as late as necessary to fix it. Really!?! Haven't we all heard, "We close at 5:00!" and been left to scramble as best we can? They were going to let us hook-up the motor-home and spend the night there, on the lot, if we wanted.  But parts were available. And they did stay until it was finished. They had offered a loaner car, but I already had made other arrangements. Who does that!?!! We arrived safely home around midnight. I am so happy we met these hard-working, honest, lovable folks! You know, people who are kind, gracious, and honestly accommodating when you are in need are REALLY SPECIAL PEOPLE.< /Review>< Response>

<pictures>None< /pictures>< text>
I've brought two different vehicles to Kennedy's for separate issues and have been throughly satisfied.  Each time I speak with Angela or Fidel, the proprietors, I get an honest assessment.  I have never felt pressured or walked away feeling I was being up-sold.  They run an efficient neighborhood shop with professionalism and warmth, and yes, this is THE place to get a quick smog check.  I highly recommend them.

Our minivan had a bad fuel pump; unfortunately our model requires accessing the pump through the cabin floor.  Not only did they do the work, they deftly handled the chaos of a minivan usually occupied by four young children and had the car seats back in place upon pick up.  More recently our sedan had a bad starter.  While making the repair, they identified a bad oil leak and a handful of other maintenance items that needed to be addressed.  While I didn't act on all of their suggestions, they still took the time to scrub my engine block clean (enough to eat off of) and even took my car through the wash!  Twice!  While I certainly don't expect such exceptional service every time, it is indicative of the kind of care they exhibit for their customers and the cars in their car.  The team at Kennedy's is solid.  They'll steer you right.</text>

I'm not usually the kind of person to write online reviews... However, Kennedy's Automotive has been such a lifesaver for me that I can't help but spread the good word!

I am a new transplant to Santa Barbara and purchased a used vehicle that turned out to have a lot of unexpected problems.

Kennedy's was recommended to me by a friend. And, after reading a few of these online reviews, it became clear that they were the kind of honest, no-pressure, no funny business kind of place I was looking for!

Angela, their office manager is such a pleasure to deal with. She's bright, bubbly, and has your best interests at heart! Her and her husband run the shop together and they're both kindhearted people who are community-focused.

This isn't the kind of place that's going to take you for a ride. This is the kind of place that will be honest with you and will work to get your car driving for most affordable price possible. It's the kind of rare business where you feel like they care about you and not your money.

Kennedy's is refreshing because they DO NOT try to upsell you. Angela is very honest about what needs to be done and makes very clear efforts to outline all your options and be realistic about your best course of action.  They do great work, but they're also looking out for you and not just trying to make a buck!

I cannot recommend them highly enough! They helped get my junker running well for a fraction of the price other garages wanted. Angela and the mechanics are all very kind, patient and wonderful people.

Obviously, three services later, I am a devoted customer. They have gone above and beyond helping me... While car repairs are always a costly pain, I've found some nice folks I feel confident and happy about giving my money to. They do an awesome job!

Give them a try, you won't be disappointed. You might even make some new friends!</review>

<Gmap_id>0x80dcdc3373ec4b61:0xc52be4cc8a2d769</Gmap_id>< review>
The prices of fuel are comparable to the other stations around the area.  Their car wash is both good and bad.  I live in an apartment, and can't wash my car in the conventional way.  I like that it's a touch-less wash (they use pressurized water).  This let me at least knock enough of the heavy dirt and dust off of my car so I could go home and use a water-less wash.  The wash does take a long time, though, so I would skip it if there was a line.</review>

< Text>
I ordered a dress from David's Bridal online. When I received it, it was too big. I scheduled an appt for alterations (bring it in at the bust, and shorten the length) and they quoted me $200. Mind you, this dress is a pretty plain, strapless bridesmaid dress with nothing fancy to it. I only paid $97 for the dress and somehow it is more to remove material than was to make the dress. Hmm. Even the original price of the dress ($130) was less than the alterations. I decided to try on different dresses in hopes that I could find one that only needed to be hemmed. But the few dresses I had to choose from were dirty and had seams coming undone. I asked if there were extra dresses and I was told that I would have to take it to a cleaners. Regardless, I would've been out the $97 I paid for the first dress because I bought it for final sale (ineligible to return). Anyway, I left and immediately called a local bridal shop, who quoted me $85 (max $100) for the alterations and yes, this shop is highly rated, so my dress will be in good hands. I have no ill feelings towards the staff, they were fine. I just want to share my experience because I know people can agree that  weddings add up. The $100-$115 savings is money I will use for my shoes and accessories.<//Text>

< text>
David’s Bridal was a very beautiful, exciting place to look for a wedding dress! They were very helpful and joined in on the fun. Although we had a really good experience, the service was disappointing. Our consultant encouraged me to get the size of the sample dress, which has been tried on my many brides, so it was very stretched. When it arrived to my house, the zippers could not zip up all the way - there about a 5 or 6 inch gap. I did receive the dress within 3 weeks of ordering it, so the likelihood of me gaining substantial weight on my waist was very slim. Additionally, our consultant did not come and measure me so that we could find out what dress size I needed to order. When we returned the dress within the 60 days and tried on a size up with a different consultant, they were not going to measure me until my Mom explicitly asked them to, which should already be done anyways since it is such a well-known dress store.
While I deeply love the gown, I was disappointed by the service and the unnecessary extra steps we needed to make in order to get the right size dress.</text>

<Text>Not going to lie - I was a bit hesitant about going to David's Bridal for wedding dress shopping.  It was my impression that it was more of a down-market strip-mall kind of place for dresses but great for bridesmaid dresses.

This location was more than a pleasant surprise - it was a WONDERFUL experience.  First, while it was in a shopping plaza, the store itself was laid out in a very inviting way with fantastic front of store/window merchandising.  The reception area is stylish and inviting.

My two besties came with for the appointment (had to be off the rack due to decision to elope).  We were placed with Stacey  as our consultant and were instantly blown away by her combination of charm, warmth, industry knowledge and professionalism.  It is a rare thing these days to be able to combine top notch customer service, mastery of an industry and the warmth and connection of a friend.  Stacey was able to establish all of this rapport with us within the first 2 minutes. She assessed my needs and went to work efficiently finding options that were available in-store for me to try.  Within 30 minutes we found the dress, 20 minutes later we were outfitted with proper accessories and walking out the door.  We had so much fun working with her and she made the experience just that - a memorable experience!

I highly recommend this location of David's Bridal, especially because of the level of excellence and service Stacey provided.<//Text>< user_name>

This is such a great DB! I had previously gone to another DB location and had completely ruled them out because I couldn’t visually see anything that appealed to me. When you’re wedding gown shopping, you can’t just see it in plastic on the rack squeezed in amongst other dresses to know exactly what it looks like. < review>
Buyers beware!!  I am really starting to think David's Bridal is about to go out of business.  If you look at their BBB complaints, they recently stopped working to resolve their complaints and now just give everyone a standard template response.  The company used to be so good at working with customers (from the complaint history up until 2 months ago all resolved) and now seem to have lost their BBB accreditation and it appears gave up on trying to resolve complaints. We are accusing David's Bridal of fraudulent business practices regarding their return policies and do not recommend doing business here.

My fiancée bought dress from David's Bridal on 10/20/2019. She went into the Arden Way location to be fitted on 3/4/2020 and dropped off the dress for alterations. Our wedding was scheduled for 4/11/2020 and the first week in March, we didn't yet know we would need to reschedule our wedding. By 03/19/2020, it was already looking like our wedding wouldn't happened so I called David's bridal to find out what to do next. They let her know that their store and alterations center had closed but took down our new wedding date of 9/6/2020 and let us know that they would contact us once they re-opened to re-fit me. Our wedding ended up being postponed a 2nd time now to 2021 so we contacted David's Bridal on 9/8/2020 to ask what we needed to do to return the dress. Keep in mind that we hadn't heard anything from them since late March when alterations were "only getting started". I am told that we can't return the dress because alterations have already been done. Knowing that the wedding was postponed and having the new date(3/19), the David's Bridal team had confirmed they would contact her for fitting before starting alterations . In addition, obviously her size is going to change over 6 months and need to be fitted again. Unless this is an error from the alterations department, it feels like alterations were started on all the dresses you already had to prevent any of your customers from returning their dresses when weddings started getting cancelled. She has lost too much weight and the dress won't fit at all. Our wedding is not the same time of year and the dress really just doesn't make sense anymore.

Yes, we have attempted to do the return through the store and corporate office and have received no help and are told that the return is outside of guidelines.  Had David's Bridal not started the alterations in error, this would be within their return policy.  We filed a BBB complaint and they didn't even look into it.  These guys are crooks.  Hopefully one of the regulatory agencies I have complained to investigate and shut them down. A lot of people are having this problem right now.< /review>

Most of this review is solely for their stylist Rebeka. She is absolutely phenomenal and I cannot say enough wonderful things about her. You can tell she genuinely loves her job and that helping you find your dress and making you feel beautiful in it is what she loves to do (and she's awesome at it). She's kind, easygoing, very friendly, and listens well. All of the dresses she suggested were beautiful and I never once felt pressured to try on or like anything I wasn't into, which has been very important to me since this whole process is very overwhelming and not really my normal scene. I'm introverted and not the best with expressing positive emotions, but she made me feel very comfortable and was easy to talk to and honest with her answers to my questions. I am so happy to have had her guidance on this journey and hope I can finally find my dress with her soon.

As for David's Bridal as a whole, the store can be completely chaotic on weekends and overwhelming for brides. Go on weekday evenings if you want a more quiet, intimate appointment. I also am not a fan of their fluctuating prices and questionably helpful staff when it gets busy. However, their dresses to tend to be on the more affordable side, which is great when you need options that don't cost $5,000.</Text>

<rating>4<//rating><review>My overall experience was a good one. I came in on a slow weeknight when there very few people in the store and was told that to even try on any dress, I would have to sign in and get a stylist. And for wedding dresses, I would need to schedule a future appointment. I felt like this was a slight inconvenience since there weren’t many people in the store and there were clearly open dressing rooms.
The woman who greets you as you walk in was not friendly at all and seemed rather annoyed to be there. I also wanted a pretty low key experience, and I was not feeling the whole check in to try on one dress and make an appointment. I understand David’s is trying to rebrand and provide more of a boutique experience, but I think having a choice would be better. Luckily, my end result was a good outcome for me.
I scheduled my bridal appointment for the weekend, and when I arrived, there were three women standing at the check-in table. There was no obvious formation of a line, so when I approached the counter, I was told that two of those three workers weren’t actually there to check people in - a task that is quite simple. The same non friendly lady from a few days back checked me in.  I was told to start browsing until my stylist found me. My stylist was amazing. Her name was Alina, and she listened to everything I said. She also listened to my budget and adhered to it 99% of the time. The only dress she brought me that was outside of my budget, she told me in advance and asked if I was interested in trying it on. The process was seamless with her help. After trying on 20 or so dresses, I finally narrowed my choices down to 3 beautiful dresses. When my appointment hour was up, Alina didn’t pressure me to purchase or to leave. I asked her to hold the dresses for me while I walked around the store to process my thoughts and make a tough decision. After I made my choice, she measured me and helped me order the correct size. It arrives in less than a month, and I couldn’t be happier with my purchase. The manager on duty was also a wonderful lady! The whole experience was an overall 8/10! Would recommend - just make an appointment and don’t worry about the non friendly attitude at the front!<//review>< pics>

<rate>1<//rate>< Review>
Last year in July 2017, I had scheduled an appt & arrived 15 minutes early.(when you walk in there is a door chimes) so I waited at the front desk, until 10 minutes AFTER my appt time had started (25 min total) I walked into the back & the worker there rudely asked, how did I get in there. I said I walked in the front door almost a half hour ago & have been waiting to check in. The attendant said, oh you don't have to check in. I said, I didn't know because I had an appointment. She laughed & said, No, I don't think you do... are you sure it was here? I said, yes, I am sure. Then I showed her my confirmation & she said, I should have your name on my appointments list. Then she walks away, grabs a clipboard & shows me the list & I show her my name RIGHT THERE ON THE APPOINTMENTS LIST.
REGARDLESS, I wasn't going to let THAT ruin my experience. So I told the worker that I was looking for something that made me look skinny-curvy but classy. I was currently 7 months pregnant & if I could find a dress design that would make me look pretty at THAT time, I would know THAT was the dress I would want to get married in after I had the baby. The lady looked at me & said well I don't know what kind that would be. Do you have any ideas? (I was shocked. Not even a suggestion. Maybe my hopes were up too high because of the show SAY YES TO THE DRESS, but this lady was making me feel like a FAT GIRL in a SKINNY PEOPLE ONLY store.) So I took out my phone & showed a few dresses of some dress designs online. The worker said, ya, we don't have anything like those. I said, I was just showing the dress shape I was looking at mostly. She said, you're welcome to look around & find something. I said, you're not going to grab me some dresses? She said, yes, sure what kinds?... I think you should wear an A-frame dress that design most women want to wear to get that shape you're looking for. I said, I don't want A-frame or ball gown because my fiance said he doesn't want anything too poofy where it would be hard to stand near me. So she said, ok, I will be back. You guys can go ahead & look while I do also. So we did. The attendant came back 5 min later with ALL A-FRAME or ball gown dresses!! I politely said, that's not what I wanted, I was looking for something more fit & flare something that hugs the body on the top a little bit doesn't really poof out at the bottom. She asked, are you going to even try any of these on? I said no, like I said, my fiance said he didn't want it to be poofy, so I don't even want to try them on, thank you. So she said she would be back with more dresses.
(Mind you, not one other customer was in the store except my wedding party)
After about 15 minutes of her gone (looking for dresses & passing by us with empty arms) & me trying 3 dresses we found ourselves, I was walking out in dresses & judging the right fit. The attendant came back, like she was putting inventory away. And Seen a couple of dresses that I asked get to pull in my size. She looked at them & said are you sure, this isn't going to give you the fit you're looking for, I mean, Iheard you say you looked too fat in the other dress & I'm just saying, this one isn't going to be more flattering. I said, it's fine. I like these, so can Ijust try them, I know I might not like it on, but Iwould like to at least try. She brought them back & basically stopped helping us from then on. We were alone, trying to figure out the front & back or which stap goes where. I began to feel defeated. I was trying on dresses for over an hour, apparently the lady who worked there was having a bad day & took it out on me.
The dresses were beautiful but not worth the experience, if it looks like I'm about to cry in some of the pictures it's because I probably was in some of them. Dress shopping should make you feel happy, it should make you want to come back. Not here< /Review>

< Text>
I am 100% in love with the wedding dress I bought from here. I just ordered it so I have not received it or experienced the alterations process yet though.

The 4 stars is for the for the fact the dressing area where we try on dresses was kind of crowded so there were people practically on top of each other. There was a group that was in our business and I’m a shy person and would have preferred more separation to make decisions and discuss with my family privately about the dresses.

My consultant was great, but she did have to bounce between me and another girl so it just seemed like every time I needed help with something she was elsewhere.

The dress selection does seem big while looking, but compared to the online store (not including what’s labeled as online only) the selection was slim... especially because I wanted to look at, and bought one of the very few, dresses that had sleeves.

Ultimately it was a decent experience. I love my dress, but just would have liked more privacy with my family to pick it. I would still recommend them to someone else.</Text>

So here's the scoop on my experience....my daughter is getting married and I needed to find that perfect dress. Upon entering David's bridal, I waited approximately 5 minutes before someone asked me what I was there for, I mentioned I had a fitting appointment, they asked for my name and said someone would be with me shortly, I mentioned I was going to browse the dresses. Found a few and 15 minutes has passed, so I saw an associate and asked how much longer, she asked me if I signed in? I said no, she said you have to sign in, so I head to the front desk, and I ask to sign in, she hands me the wrong sign in sheet, and I mentioned to her, that she has already been taken my name, I'm just waiting on a fitting specialist. She said one will be with me shortly. I went and sat down for about 5 minutes, then a young lady greeted me and showed me the fitting room, I tried on the dresses I picked out! Yes I found the dress!! I then go to check out, and I wait..wait...then out the door I go, I was never measured, didn't have one dress brought to me, but in the end I did find the perfect dress. It seemed to me that they were disorganized, and yes, I was a mother of a bride, not a bride, but i had an appointment. Good luck and have lots if patience when you go, I guarantee you'll find that perfect dress<//Review>

<Name>B-Ren P</Name><time>1579805999988</time><Rating>5<//Rating>< review>
My family and I are regular clients of David’s Bridal for many years now, we have purchased several wedding gowns and special occasion dresses from this location. This past Christmas my sister got engaged and to our surprise they want a wedding very soon. We booked an appointment and where very fortunate to get Lou as our bridal consultant.This woman is the best bridal consultant we have ever interacted with, not only at davids bridal but other high end bridal boutiques. Her costumer service is superb. She listened to all of my sister requests and also handled the rest of the bridal parties opinions and questions with a great attitude and professionalism. My sister found a dress but wasn't sold on it and wanted to sleep on it before making the purchase. Lou assured her that she was totally fine doing so and she completely understood. She scheduled a follow up to return and try it on again, Lou let her know she would have more options for her in case she was interested in trying on some other styles. Between that day and the weekend I had to reach out to Alison the store manager due to a different situation that I needed her help with which I wont go into details for however I have to mention Alison in this review due to the fact that she made a very remarkable impression on how she handled the situation I brought to her attention. She took ownership of the situation and made it right as soon as I explained it to her over the phone. Alison is prime example of a leader by her making sure we where taken care she retained us as costumers. She saved the relationship of our family with this company. Not only did she handle the situation like a professional but did it with grace and great costumer service. Often times when you bring a issue to a manager they can be standoffish and offended. David’s Bridal is very lucky to have Alison and Lou at this location, Alison with her leadership and knowledge, and Lou with her personality and work ethic make this location five stars.
When we returned to the follow up appointment Lou greeted us and went right to work, while always remaining as pleasant as the first interaction as someone who trains in sales I understand that Lou could have been working with another bride, you can tell she loves what she does and treats all costumers like she would like to be treated. I can’t thank Lou enough for her help and the great experience she created for not only my sister but my entire family. Lou has earned our business and will be back in the future when we need dresses for our special events. Oh and yes, my disorder found the perfect dress thanks to Lou! You are THE BEST LOU! THANK YOU!< /review>

<username>Paige Jewell< /username><Date>1576030227626<//Date><Rate>1<//Rate><review>I made an appointment, and had a very terrible experience. So bad that I left and placed the order for my bridesmaid dress online.

I was there at 10:30 AM, and I was the only one in the store. 2 employees were working - my "designer," and the lady that stands in front. My designer was a lady that helped me pick the dresses to try (I could get any style just had to be the correct color), but told me my size wasn't avail in all styles so she said she'd "clip the bigger sizes." I got dresses from 2-6, which is actually quite a large range.

The dresses here are firstly, so gross. They have sweat and deodorant stains, and are stretched from years of ppl trying them on. This I guess just comes with the territory, but gross. Most of the eye hooks are broken, so you can't even get a feel for the neckline/delicate piece that has the hook. You just have to hold it together with your hands and try to picture yourself in that dress with it hooked, so ghetto. The lady was never around to help so yes, I literally had to hold the neckline together with my hands and try to look at myself.

Upon trying them on for my appointment, I actually just ended up trying it all on alone. I'd put one on, walk around the store looking for the stylist, who was NEVER AROUND. Then she'd find me looking, offer some feedback and once I went back in the fitting room she'd say "I'll be right back," but she was NEVER RIGHT BACK! I zipped all 10 dresses on myself, did a spin and told myself what looked good and what didn't. What was the point of making an appointment to get help? She literally wasted so much time in my day, as I just kept waiting like an idiot. The lady in front was actually more helpful because I knew where to find her to ask for advice.

All in all, the lady supposed to be helping me never "clipped the dresses to make them fit," never helped zip the tight ones with tall zippers, or really assisted in my experience. I had the most terrible time, and it put me in the worst mood that I couldn't even smile or enjoy the experience. I wish I had never made an appointment and wasted 1.5 hours trying dresses on alone in an empty store. I can't even imagine how bad the service would be if there were more brides/bridesmaids.

I ordered online, and customer support on the phone was nice so I 100% recommend that and not going in the store. I will never return here.<//review>< pics>

< Text>
This store is bright and clean with lots of dresses displayed. I absolutely loved the atmosphere and everyone was very helpful! It was my first time looking for a dress and I had a very specific look in mind since I will be getting married in Hawaii. I only have limited time and was hoping I could find a dress the same day. At the same time, I was also hoping that I could still have that bridal experience and feel like I also found "the one"! <review>LOVE, LOVE, LOVE the staff at David’s Bridal Sacramento!!! I started shopping for my dress in June 2019 for my beach destination wedding this March. Sharee (the manager), Isabel, Morgan, another manager and a few other sales consultants (whose names I forgot, my sincere apologies ) all helped me willingly each time I came in for an appointment.  They never complained when assisting me find the dress of my dreams but instead made me feel welcome which really helped to alleviate my stress.  Not one person made me feel like I was bothersome although I kept apologizing for changing my mind.  I came to the store so much that they remembered me by name.  I even called to set up another appointment an hour after my alterations pinning session for my fourth dress because family members liked another dress I had tried on after showing them the pictures.  Sharee was happy to assist and asked Morgan if she can come in the next day to help me.  Morgan agreed even though she was not scheduled to work!! How awesome is that? < review>
I went to this David’s Bridal location on 06/02/2018 on the search for my MOH dress and the whole process was fantastic! I called about 2 weeks in advance to get setup for a try-on session so I’d have a stylist to assist me; from scheduling that to the moment I checked out at the store, it was a divine experience. The 2 ladies available at check-in were very polite/professional/complimentary  first thing in the morning. I was assisted promptly and allowed to explore the floor while I waited for my stylist. I was paired with Kendra who was amazing! She took the time to hear about my styling needs/personal preference and allowed me to kind of “do my own thing” (at my request). I tried on about 10 different dresses, some David’s Bridal brands and some designer, with a positive experience and ended up buying the perfect dress. Kendra checked in on me on multiple occasions, asking if unneeded anything, offering styling/comfortability advice, etc. while also assisting other brides/parties. I had questions about potential alterations and was allowed to speak with the adorable seamstress who provided honest feedback.

TOTALLY AMAZING EXPERIENCE and would highly recommend this location and these ladies as they made what could have been a disaster rather enjoyable!

The only 2 things I’d work on from a store perspective would be the cleanliness of the fitting rooms and bathroom. None “horrible” but there was evidence of glitter/fabric strings from other try-on sessions and the bathroom could have had some TLC.< /review>

< Review>
I had an appointment at David's Bridal on Arden Way at 9:30 a.m. on a Saturday morning. We had two flower girls, both age 5 and their mothers. The room was too small to fit all of them in at once, and we wanted them to try the dresses on simultaneously since they were going to be wearing the same dress for the wedding. We were only given one room and no one else was in our area at the time, so we took another room. Our stylist said if the other appointment arrives, we would need to give up the room we took because we were only given one room. We should have been given two rooms. While the girls were trying on the dresses, we saw our stylist maybe two or three times. She really wasn't present for our appointment as she was busy with another appointment. She had to keep stepping away and when she was ringing me up for the two flower girl dresses, she had to call another staff to help me finish my transaction for the second dress. Overall, the customer service could have been a lot better. I don't really understand why David's Bridal doesn't devote one person to one appointment.<//Review>

<Review>I had the loveliest experience at the Arden David’s Bridal! I came from out of town and came with my mom and two sisters. Our stylist Lanea was lovely and such a help. After a quick scroll through my Pinterest board and a whirl around the showroom I had six dresses to try on.

There were plenty of accessories to help complete the look. Belts and veils helped me see “the whole picture” when trying on a dress. All the other stylists in the store were so warm and friendly, offering their own feedback on the dresses i was trying on.

As a plus size bride, wedding dress shopping was what I was least looking forward to about the planning process. The fact that dresses were in my size, not a sample I squeezed into like sausage casing, made me feel feel so much more confident and pretty!

I left with not one but two dresses! I can’t speak highly enough of my David’s experience! I’m a wedding industry professional who knows what a stressful experience the planning process can be. David’s help me happily and confidently check the dress off my list! Thank you!< /Review>< Date>

< rate>

<review>I wasn't incredibly impressed with my experience here. Earlier this year, I went in with a friend who is getting married and helped her pick out a dress -- she seemed really excited and happy when she walked out of there. So when I got engaged, I thought, "I'll go back and hopefully feel the same way!" Not so.

I'm not sure if it's the time of year or what, but they had hardly any dresses in my size, which the stylist said is pretty popular. It IS right after Christmas so I'll give DB the benefit of the doubt on that one. Still, pretty disappointing when you have a 90-minute appointment and there are like 6 things to try on.

Another thing is our stylist was 20 minutes late to help us and then was in a big rush at the end to wrap it up. When you advertise 90-minute appointments, make it 90 minutes.

She also really wasn't around that much. There was a lot of waiting around between dresses, just standing awkwardly in half-zipped monstrosities, while she brought new stuff to try on. Again, maybe this was part of not having a lot in my size and she was looking for more. But it was still pretty awkward and my friend ended up having to do a lot of the zipping/buttoning/tugging.

Another thing is she kept bringing me these HUGE DRESSES. I told her right off the bat that we were having an outdoor, relatively informal wedding. Boom -- ball gowns. Ball gowns after ball gowns. With enormous trains. I appreciated being able to try on some things I wouldn't normally through her suggestions and it was fun to try on the first big, poofy, princess dress. But overall, I did not feel listened to.

And finally, what really solidified the whole underwhelming experience was when we were talking about my wedding, which isn't for another year and a half. I was casually mentioning (again) how it would be outdoors and informal and that our guest list really wasn't that big. And she said, "Well, your guest list isn't that big NOW."

Nope. Do not stand here and tell me what sort of wedding I want. Not all of us want big, sparkly princess weddings with $80,000 budgets and 300 guests. I'm getting married on a budget, on a lakeshore in October, surrounded by 40 of my/my partner's closest friends and relatives. Then we're going to a local brewery for the reception. A ball gown's just not gonna cut it, but thanks anyway.

Maybe most of these issues stemmed from a lack of dresses in my size and I can absolutely work with that. It happens, especially right after Christmas. But the not-feeling-listened-to part? Nah. I won't be back here.< /review>< Pictures>
None</Pictures>

< review>
When I first got there I was a little confused as to where to go: if I was supposed to follow the lady, etc. but that was a quick solve. We headed to the back where the clearance was and picked out dresses. Mariah quickly came over and put them by my door to try them on. She was very quick to ask how things were and if I needed help and also for bringing a variety of accessories like a belt and a veil that really added to the dress. When I found a dress that was too expensive on accident, she found me another that was cheaper, but similar and I absolutely loved it! I definitely went in thinking this place was a chain and that I wouldn't like it, but they have tons of selection (which was a huge perk) and the staff was bubbly and helpful. I would recommend to anyone going dress shopping.<//review>

<user_name>Cristi G< /user_name><Rate>5<//Rate><Gmap_id>0x809ada186eab51a3:0xfa030371756ca2ef< /Gmap_id><text>I purchased my wedding dress from the Modesto location a few weeks ago and was hesitant to branch out to a different store for the bridesmaids dresses. My bridesmaids and I  looked at a few places near our homes. I have one bridemaid who is plus sized and she was treated very differently at a few bridal stores and they had nothing for her to try on.  That made me feel terrible. We decided we would check out the Sacramento David’s Bridal since we had such a great experience in Modesto and this was closer. I trust David’s bridal because they have sizes up to 30 and they are reliable. I made an appointment and unfortunately, I had to work a little later which pushed us all back to arriving about 30 minutes past that time slot. I called the store and Rebecca (sorry if I misspelled) answered and explained that they would do their best to help us. We still went, and they really did a great job helping my bridesmaids and I. The store is gorgouse and had a large selection. Mariah was our stylist and she assisted my four bridesmaids in finding dresses. All of these women have very different body types and I was nervous about finding something that would work for everyone. Mariah gave ideas as far as what to try on, grabbed many dresses at a time for them, and was extremely attentive. She was an excellent sales consultant and treated us very well. She smiled, made eye contact, and was very patient the entire time. They must have tried on about 12 different styles. They were all eventually able to find a dress that worked for each one and I just want to thank the staff at this store for accommodating us and for assisting us in this purchase. I’m so pleased with our visit !

Fast forward many months, I went to alterations to pick up my dress. Zahra was amazing ! Friendly, kind, and had great customer service. Will definitely recommend !</text></record>
